          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the streusel",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{plain-flour}} for the streusel, {{light-brown-sugar}}, and {{cinnamon-ground}} in a bowl. Add the cold {{unsalted-butter}} for the streusel and rub it in with your fingertips until the mixture forms irregular clumps. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "streusel",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yfzbd000040v4dwcbk1a2"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Refrigerate while you make the cake batter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Butter and line the square tin. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} for the cake with the {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}} for the cake, {{baking-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} alternately with the {{whole-milk}}, beginning and ending with the flour. Pour into the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top and bake, 35 to 38 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Scatter the streusel evenly over the top of the batter and press it in lightly. Bake for 35 to 38 minutes until a skewer inserted into the centre of the cake (not the streusel) comes out clean. The streusel should be deep brown and crisp. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes before cutting into squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
